        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "[Original message by Michael Depetrillo|http:\/\/www.nabble.com\/zend_db_table-and-zend_db_select-tf3673528s16154.html#a10264936]:\n\nHello\n\nI was wondering if it made sense to add a select($cols) helper method to\nZend_Db_Table that would return an instance of Zend_Db_Select.\n\nExample:\n{code}\n<?php\nModel_Lead extends Zend_Db_Table_Abstract { $_name = 'leads_table'; }\n\n$lead = new Model_Lead();\n$select = $lead->select(new Zend_Db_Expr('COUNT(*)')->where('status = ?', 'pending');\necho $select; \/\/ select COUNT(*) from leads_table\n?>\n{code}\n\nThis would be very helpful in centralizing tables names through models."
        },
