        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14411",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=klassicd",
                        "name": "klassicd",
                        "displayName": "michael depetrillo",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There was a typo in my original message.  The example above should return \"select count(*) from leads_table where status = ?\".",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=klassicd",
                        "name": "klassicd",
                        "displayName": "michael depetrillo",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-01T12:18:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-01T12:18:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/14415",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "A workaround that exists right now is the following:\n\n{code}\n$lead = new Model_Lead();\n$select = $lead->getAdapter()->select();\n$select->from($lead->info()['name'], 'COUNT(*)');\n$select->where('status = ?', 'pending');\n{code}\n\nThis issue is related to ZF-836, which requests a feature of a table method fetchCount().\n\nWe aren't going to address this use case in ZF 1.0.  We would like to provide a solution later, but I'm going to postpone this issue for now.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-05-01T13:46:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-05-01T13:46:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18610",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=peptolab",
                        "name": "peptolab",
                        "displayName": "Simon Mundy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "With the new Zend_Db_Table enhancements you can now perform\n{code}\n$lead = new Model_Lead();\n$select = $lead->select();\n$select->from($lead, 'COUNT(*)')->where('status = ?', 'pending');\n{code}\nDoes that satisfy the requirements of this request? If so I'll mark it as complete.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=peptolab",
                        "name": "peptolab",
                        "displayName": "Simon Mundy",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-01-26T17:45:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-01-26T17:45:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/27498",
